Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_opt_slack_weighting_factor(25.10)    set_opt_slack_weighting_factor(25.10)

Name
       set_opt_slack_weighting_factor  -  Specifies view-based slack weighting
       factor for setup and hold modes

Syntax
        set_opt_slack_weighting_factor

       [-help]<factor>

       [-hold]

       [-setup]

       -view <view_name>

       Specifies view-based slack weighting factor for setup and  hold  modes.
       If neither -setup nor -hold parameters are specified, the weight slack-
       ing  factor  is applied to both. This command is relevant only when the
       following mode is used:

       setDesignMode -slackWeighting viewBasedWeighting

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_opt_slack_weighting_factor parameter. For
              a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the  man command:

               man set_opt_slack_weighting_factor

       <factor>
              Specifies  the  view-based slack weighting factor to apply. This
              is a required parameter.

       -hold  Specifies that slack weighting factor should be applied to  hold
              mode for the specified view.

       -setup Specifies that slack weighting factor should be applied to setup
              mode for the specified view.

       -view <view_name>
              Specifies  the view for which slack weights are defined. This is
              a required parameter.

Example
       Use the below command to set the slack weigting factor for  the  speci-
       fied setup view to 0.8.

       set_opt_slack_weighting_factor -view setup_func 0.8 -setup

Related Information
              * The following chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * Optimizing Timing

